defs.docs:
This crate is a Rust port of Google's high-performance [SwissTable] hash
 map, adapted to make it a drop-in replacement for Rust's standard `HashMap`
 and `HashSet` types.

defs.name: FxHashBuilder
defs.docs: Type alias for a `HashBuilder` using the `fx` hash algorithm.

defs.name: FxHasher
defs.docs:
A speedy hash algorithm for use within rustc. The hashmap in liballoc
 by default uses SipHash which isn't quite as speedy as we want. In the
 compiler we're not really worried about DOS attempts, so we use a fast
 non-cryptographic hash.

defs.name: HashMap
defs.docs: A hash map implemented with quadratic probing and SIMD lookup.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty `HashMap`.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Creates an empty `HashMap` with the specified capacity.

defs.name: with_hasher
defs.docs:
Creates an empty `HashMap` which will use the given hash builder to hash
 keys.

defs.name: with_capacity_and_hasher
defs.docs:
Creates an empty `HashMap` with the specified capacity, using `hash_builder`
 to hash the keys.

defs.name: hasher
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the map's [`BuildHasher`].

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements the map can hold without reallocating.

defs.name: keys
defs.docs:
An iterator visiting all keys in arbitrary order.
 The iterator element type is `&'a K`.

defs.name: values
defs.docs:
An iterator visiting all values in arbitrary order.
 The iterator element type is `&'a V`.

defs.name: values_mut
defs.docs:
An iterator visiting all values mutably in arbitrary order.
 The iterator element type is `&'a mut V`.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs:
An iterator visiting all key-value pairs in arbitrary order.
 The iterator element type is `(&'a K, &'a V)`.

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs:
An iterator visiting all key-value pairs in arbitrary order,
 with mutable references to the values.
 The iterator element type is `(&'a K, &'a mut V)`.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the map.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the map contains no elements.

defs.name: drain
defs.docs:
Clears the map, returning all key-value pairs as an iterator. Keeps the
 allocated memory for reuse.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs:
Clears the map, removing all key-value pairs. Keeps the allocated memory
 for reuse.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted
 in the `HashMap`. The collection may reserve more space to avoid
 frequent reallocations.

defs.name: try_reserve
defs.value: fn (&mut self, additional: usize) -> Result<(), CollectionAllocErr>
defs.docs:
Tries to reserve capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted
 in the given `HashMap<K,V>`. The collection may reserve more space to avoid
 frequent reallocations.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the map as much as possible. It will drop
 down as much as possible while maintaining the internal rules
 and possibly leaving some space in accordance with the resize policy.

defs.name: shrink_to
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the map with a lower limit. It will drop
 down no lower than the supplied limit while maintaining the internal rules
 and possibly leaving some space in accordance with the resize policy.

defs.name: entry
defs.value: fn (&mut self, key: K) -> Entry<'_, K, V, S>
defs.docs: Gets the given key's corresponding entry in the map for in-place manipulation.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value corresponding to the key.

defs.name: get_key_value
defs.docs: Returns the key-value pair corresponding to the supplied key.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the map contains a value for the specified key.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the value corresponding to the key.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, k: K, v: V) -> Option<V>
defs.docs: Inserts a key-value pair into the map.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes a key from the map, returning the value at the key if the key
 was previously in the map.

defs.name: remove_entry
defs.docs:
Removes a key from the map, returning the stored key and value if the
 key was previously in the map.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: raw_entry_mut
defs.value: fn (&mut self) -> RawEntryBuilderMut<'_, K, V, S>
defs.docs: Creates a raw entry builder for the HashMap.

defs.name: raw_entry
defs.docs: Creates a raw immutable entry builder for the HashMap.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over the entries of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: IterMut
defs.docs: A mutable iterator over the entries of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An owning iterator over the entries of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over the keys of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over the values of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator over the entries of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: ValuesMut
defs.docs: A mutable iterator over the values of a `HashMap`.

defs.name: RawEntryBuilderMut
defs.docs: A builder for computing where in a [`HashMap`] a key-value pair would be stored.

defs.name: Occupied
defs.docs: An occupied entry.

defs.name: Vacant
defs.docs: A vacant entry.

defs.name: RawEntryMut
defs.docs: A view into a single entry in a map, which may either be vacant or occupied.

defs.name: RawOccupiedEntryMut
defs.docs:
A view into an occupied entry in a `HashMap`.
 It is part of the [`RawEntryMut`] enum.

defs.name: RawVacantEntryMut
defs.docs:
A view into a vacant entry in a `HashMap`.
 It is part of the [`RawEntryMut`] enum.

defs.name: RawEntryBuilder
defs.docs: A builder for computing where in a [`HashMap`] a key-value pair would be stored.

defs.name: from_key
defs.value: fn <Q> (self, k: &Q) -> RawEntryMut<'a, K, V, S>
defs.docs: Creates a `RawEntryMut` from the given key.

defs.name: from_key_hashed_nocheck
defs.value: fn <Q> (self, hash: u64, k: &Q) -> RawEntryMut<'a, K, V, S>
defs.docs: Creates a `RawEntryMut` from the given key and its hash.

defs.name: from_hash
defs.value: fn <F> (self, hash: u64, is_match: F) -> RawEntryMut<'a, K, V, S>
defs.docs: Creates a `RawEntryMut` from the given hash.

defs.name: from_key
defs.docs: Access an entry by key.

defs.name: from_key_hashed_nocheck
defs.value: fn <Q> (self, hash: u64, k: &Q) -> Option<(&'a K, &'a V)>
defs.docs: Access an entry by a key and its hash.

defs.name: from_hash
defs.value: fn <F> (self, hash: u64, is_match: F) -> Option<(&'a K, &'a V)>
defs.docs: Access an entry by hash.

defs.name: or_insert
defs.value: fn (self, default_key: K, default_val: V) -> (&'a mut K, &'a mut V)
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the default if empty, and returns
 mutable references to the key and value in the entry.

defs.name: or_insert_with
defs.value: fn <F> (self, default: F) -> (&'a mut K, &'a mut V)
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the result of the default function if empty,
 and returns mutable references to the key and value in the entry.

defs.name: and_modify
defs.docs:
Provides in-place mutable access to an occupied entry before any
 potential inserts into the map.

defs.name: key
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the key in the entry.

defs.name: key_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the key in the entry.

defs.name: into_key
defs.docs:
Converts the entry into a mutable reference to the key in the entry
 with a lifetime bound to the map itself.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: into_mut
defs.docs:
Converts the OccupiedEntry into a mutable reference to the value in the entry
 with a lifetime bound to the map itself.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: get_key_value
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the key and value in the entry.

defs.name: get_key_value_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the key and value in the entry.

defs.name: into_key_value
defs.docs:
Converts the OccupiedEntry into a mutable reference to the key and value in the entry
 with a lifetime bound to the map itself.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs: Sets the value of the entry, and returns the entry's old value.

defs.name: insert_key
defs.docs: Sets the value of the entry, and returns the entry's old value.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Takes the value out of the entry, and returns it.

defs.name: remove_entry
defs.docs: Take the ownership of the key and value from the map.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (self, key: K, value: V) -> (&'a mut K, &'a mut V)
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the VacantEntry's key,
 and returns a mutable reference to it.

defs.name: insert_hashed_nocheck
defs.value: fn (self, hash: u64, key: K, value: V) -> (&'a mut K, &'a mut V)
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the VacantEntry's key,
 and returns a mutable reference to it.

defs.name: insert_with_hasher
defs.value: fn <H> (self, hash: u64, key: K, value: V, hasher: H) -> (&'a mut K, &'a mut V)
defs.docs: Set the value of an entry with a custom hasher function.

defs.name: Occupied
defs.docs: An occupied entry.

defs.name: Vacant
defs.docs: A vacant entry.

defs.name: Entry
defs.docs: A view into a single entry in a map, which may either be vacant or occupied.

defs.name: OccupiedEntry
defs.docs:
A view into an occupied entry in a `HashMap`.
 It is part of the [`Entry`] enum.

defs.name: VacantEntry
defs.docs:
A view into a vacant entry in a `HashMap`.
 It is part of the [`Entry`] enum.

defs.name: or_insert
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the default if empty, and returns
 a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: or_insert_with
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the result of the default function if empty,
 and returns a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: key
defs.docs: Returns a reference to this entry's key.

defs.name: and_modify
defs.docs:
Provides in-place mutable access to an occupied entry before any
 potential inserts into the map.

defs.name: or_default
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the default value if empty,
 and returns a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: key
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the key in the entry.

defs.name: remove_entry
defs.docs: Take the ownership of the key and value from the map.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: into_mut
defs.docs:
Converts the OccupiedEntry into a mutable reference to the value in the entry
 with a lifetime bound to the map itself.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, mut value: V) -> V
defs.docs: Sets the value of the entry, and returns the entry's old value.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Takes the value out of the entry, and returns it.

defs.name: replace_entry
defs.docs:
Replaces the entry, returning the old key and value. The new key in the hash map will be
 the key used to create this entry.

defs.name: replace_key
defs.docs: Replaces the key in the hash map with the key used to create this entry.

defs.name: key
defs.docs:
Gets a reference to the key that would be used when inserting a value
 through the `VacantEntry`.

defs.name: into_key
defs.docs: Take ownership of the key.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the VacantEntry's key,
 and returns a mutable reference to it.

defs.name: HashSet
defs.docs: A hash set implemented as a `HashMap` where the value is `()`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty `HashSet`.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Creates an empty `HashSet` with the specified capacity.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements the set can hold without reallocating.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs:
An iterator visiting all elements in arbitrary order.
 The iterator element type is `&'a T`.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the set.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the set contains no elements.

defs.name: drain
defs.docs: Clears the set, returning all elements in an iterator.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the set, removing all values.

defs.name: with_hasher
defs.docs:
Creates a new empty hash set which will use the given hasher to hash
 keys.

defs.name: with_capacity_and_hasher
defs.docs:
Creates an empty `HashSet` with the specified capacity, using
 `hasher` to hash the keys.

defs.name: hasher
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the set's [`BuildHasher`].

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted
 in the `HashSet`. The collection may reserve more space to avoid
 frequent reallocations.

defs.name: try_reserve
defs.value: fn (&mut self, additional: usize) -> Result<(), CollectionAllocErr>
defs.docs:
Tries to reserve capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted
 in the given `HashSet<K,V>`. The collection may reserve more space to avoid
 frequent reallocations.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the set as much as possible. It will drop
 down as much as possible while maintaining the internal rules
 and possibly leaving some space in accordance with the resize policy.

defs.name: shrink_to
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the set with a lower limit. It will drop
 down no lower than the supplied limit while maintaining the internal rules
 and possibly leaving some space in accordance with the resize policy.

defs.name: difference
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a Self) -> Difference<'a, T, S>
defs.docs:
Visits the values representing the difference,
 i.e., the values that are in `self` but not in `other`.

defs.name: symmetric_difference
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a Self) -> SymmetricDifference<'a, T, S>
defs.docs:
Visits the values representing the symmetric difference,
 i.e., the values that are in `self` or in `other` but not in both.

defs.name: intersection
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a Self) -> Intersection<'a, T, S>
defs.docs:
Visits the values representing the intersection,
 i.e., the values that are both in `self` and `other`.

defs.name: union
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a Self) -> Union<'a, T, S>
defs.docs:
Visits the values representing the union,
 i.e., all the values in `self` or `other`, without duplicates.

defs.name: contains
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the set contains a value.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value in the set, if any, that is equal to the given value.

defs.name: is_disjoint
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if `self` has no elements in common with `other`.
 This is equivalent to checking for an empty intersection.

defs.name: is_subset
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if the set is a subset of another,
 i.e., `other` contains at least all the values in `self`.

defs.name: is_superset
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if the set is a superset of another,
 i.e., `self` contains at least all the values in `other`.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs: Adds a value to the set.

defs.name: replace
defs.docs:
Adds a value to the set, replacing the existing value, if any, that is equal to the given
 one. Returns the replaced value.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes a value from the set. Returns whether the value was
 present in the set.

defs.name: take
defs.docs: Removes and returns the value in the set, if any, that is equal to the given one.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over the items of a `HashSet`.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An owning iterator over the items of a `HashSet`.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator over the items of a `HashSet`.

defs.name: Intersection
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the intersection of `HashSet`s.

defs.name: Difference
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the difference of `HashSet`s.

defs.name: SymmetricDifference
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the symmetric difference of `HashSet`s.

defs.name: Union
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the union of `HashSet`s.

defs.name: hash_map
defs.docs: A hash map implemented with quadratic probing and SIMD lookup.

defs.name: hash_set
defs.docs: A hash set implemented as a `HashMap` where the value is `()`.

defs.name: CapacityOverflow
defs.docs:
Error due to the computed capacity exceeding the collection's maximum
 (usually `isize::MAX` bytes).

defs.name: AllocErr
defs.docs: Error due to the allocator (see the `AllocErr` type's docs).

defs.name: CollectionAllocErr
defs.docs: Augments `AllocErr` with a `CapacityOverflow` variant.
